The paper deals with image fusion and super-resolution, which are topics commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The use of regularization and optimization techniques also suggests that the paper could belong to the information theory (cs.IT) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the application of the proposed method to remote sensing data implies that it could also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
